description.en:
This is a knowledge model that aims to provide the 
                                    taxonomy and  vocabulary to describe the Environmental Product 
                                    Declaration of building materials and products,with their corresponding
                                    properties and individuals relevant within the construction industry 
                                    as found within the available open databases. This is developed to 
                                    closely follow the EPD+ILCD Format so that it can be used for semantic 
                                    interoperability solutions within the knowledge domain

description.undefined: This class encompasses additional environmental impact indicators that extend beyond the core mandatory impact categories required by EPD standards. These may include specialized impact categories such as human toxicity potential, ecotoxicity potential, ionizing radiation potential, land use impacts, fossil resource scarcity, and other emerging impact categories. These additional indicators provide a more comprehensive environmental assessment and may be required by specific EPD programs or building certification schemes.
Potential Human Exposure Efficiency Relative to U235 (IRP) quantifies human exposure efficiency concerning uranium-235. The specific unit is "kBq U235-eq".

labels.en: Potential Human exposure efficiency relative to U235 (IRP)

description.undefined: Potential Incidence of Disease Due to PM Emissions (PM) gauges the likelihood of diseases occurring due to particulate matter emissions. There is no specific unit for potential incidence of disease.

labels.en: Potential Incidence of Disease due to PM Emissions (PM)

description.undefined: Potential Comparative Toxic Unit for Humans - Cancer Effects (HTP-c) quantifies a substance's potential toxicity to humans, specifically concerning cancer. The specific unit for potential comparative toxic units for human - cancer effects is "CTUh".

labels.en: Potential Comparative Toxic Unit for humans cancer effects (HTP c)

description.undefined: Potential Comparative Toxic Unit for Humans - Non-Cancer Effects (HTP-nc) quantifies a substance's potential toxicity to humans, excluding cancer-related effects. The specific unit for potential comparative toxic units for humans - non-cancer effects is "CTUh".

labels.en: Potential Comparative Toxic Unit for humans non-cancer effects (HTP nc)

description.undefined: Potential Comparative Toxic Unit for Ecosystems (ETP-fw) measures a substance's potential toxicity to ecosystems. The specific unit is "CTUe".

labels.en: Potential Comparative Toxic Unit for ecosystems (ETP fw)

description.undefined: Potential Soil Quality Index (SQP) provides an index indicating the potential impact of a substance on soil quality. There is no specific unit for potential soil quality index.

comment.undefined: Supplementary environmental impact indicators beyond the core mandatory impact categories

description.undefined: This class represents indicators that describe the output flows related to waste generation and disposal throughout the life cycle of a building product or material. These indicators include quantities of hazardous waste disposed, non-hazardous waste disposed, radioactive waste disposed, materials for recycling, materials for energy recovery, and components for re-use. These outputs are essential for understanding the end-of-life environmental implications and circular economy potential of building materials.
Exported Electrical Energy (EEE) represents electrical energy exported to external systems. The unit for exported electrical energy is typically "MJ" (megajoules).
